memberdef.name: createDatasource

detaileddescription.para: This method creates a new data source. According to the specified data source category, the connection to the data source will be tested within this method. If the test does not pass the credentials will not be stored and the reponse status code will be set to 422.
Currently, the default MongoDB data source cannot be created using this method.

parameterdescription.para: The name of the data source. The data source name can contain any alphabetic letter, numbers, dots, or dashes, and must start with an alphabetic letter.
Whether the new data source will be the default one for its category. The default value is false.
The data sources credentials as JSON.

memberdef.name: updateDatasource

detaileddescription.para: This method updates a data source changing its name, whether it is default or not, or its credentials. At least one change, that is, one of the optional parameters, must be specified.
Currently, the default MongoDB data source cannot be modified through this method.

parameterdescription.para: The new name of the data source. If not specified the data source is not renamed.
Whether the data source should become (if true) or cease to be (if false) the default one for its category. If not specified the data source does not change its default status.
The new data sources credentials as JSON. If not specified the data sources credentials are not changed
